Port Elizabeth police have asked for the community’s assistance in locating a teenage girl from Soweto-on-Sea who has been missing since the weekend. Zenathi Bekela, 13,  left her Luwela Street home on Saturday at 2pm after informing her aunt that she was going to visit a friend nearby. She never returned home and has not been seen since. Her mother reported her missing on Monday. She was wearing a grey top, black jeans and pink sandals when she was last seen. Anyone with information about Zenathi’s whereabouts can contact Detective Sergeant Jerome Jacobs on 071-475-2324, or contact their nearest police station. HeraldLIVE